{{Other uses|Oyama Shrine (disambiguation){{!}}Oyama Shrine}}{{Short description|Shinto shrine in Ishikawa Prefecture, Japan}} {{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|'''Oyama Shrine'''|尾山神社|Oyama-jinja}} | image = Kanazawa-C-2852.jpg | caption = Main gate | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|36|33|59|N|136|39|19|E|type:landmark_region:JP|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = 1599 | date_destroyed = | location = [[Kanazawa, Ishikawa]], [[Japan]]. | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} [[Image:Oyama Shrine (Ishikawa).jpg|thumbnail|Oyama-jinja]] {{nihongo|'''Oyama Shrine'''|尾山神社|Oyama-jinja}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Kanazawa, Ishikawa]], [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-06-06 |title=A Summer Stroll Through Green Kanazawa |url=https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-video/ct171000015/a-summer-stroll-through-green-kanazawa.html |access-date=2022-11-04 |website=nippon.com |language=en}}</ref>
The shrine was established in 1599, dedicated to [[Maeda Toshiie]] (the first lord of [[Kaga Domain]]), in [[Mount Utatsu|Utatsu-yama]] (卯辰山), east of [[Kanazawa, Ishikawa|Kanazawa]]. It was moved to its present location in 1873 and renamed to '''Oyama-jinja'''. The main gate was constructed in 1875. This gate is a peculiar mix of traditional [[Art and architecture of Japan|Japanese]], [[Culture of China|Chinese]], and [[Architectural style|European]] religious [[Architecture|architectural]] elements. The gate is {{convert|25|m}} high including the [[lightning rod]]. The third floor is particular famous for its [[Netherlands|Dutch]] stained-glass windows. It is said that the third floor was also used as a [[lighthouse]]. The gate was designated an [[Important Cultural Properties of Japan|Important Cultural Asset]] on August 29, 1950.
